    {
      "key": "f2acf7aa-6706-4e66-ad9d-e338ca035d6d",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display**: Show “Reflect” slide\n\n\n**Reflect:** *What is another shape or figure you could program using loops? What is the code you used to create it?*",
        "name": "Reflection"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f2acf7aa-6706-4e66-ad9d-e338ca035d6d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5bea1989-44a4-427f-ad6b-dd5ae9d6fa86"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "0614db28-12c1-4e17-a86d-d1257db26838",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display**: Show “Reflect” slide\n\nBriefly review with the class what loops are and why we use them.\n\n - _What do loops do?_\n    - Loops repeat a set of commands.\n - _How do we use loops?_\n    - We use loops to create a pattern made of repeated actions.\n\n&nbsp\n\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display**: Show “Looping a Loop” slide\n\n\nTell the class that they will now be doing something super cool: using loops inside loops.\n\n**Say:** *Can you predict what kinds of things we would be using a loop inside of a loop for?*\n\n_If a loop repeats a pattern, then looping a loop would repeat a pattern of patterns!_\n\n&nbsp\n\nStudents don't need to understand this right away, so feel free to move on to the online puzzles even if students still seem a little confused.",
        "name": "Introduction\r"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "0614db28-12c1-4e17-a86d-d1257db26838",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5f4ff1f4-7394-4cdd-be9b-41621babf395"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "233eb40b-97b7-4408-9bf5-194520ea12a5",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "###Vocabulary\n\n&nbsp\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display**: Show “Vocabulary” slide\n\n- **Command** - An instruction for the computer. \n\n- **Loop** - The action of doing something over and over again.\n- **Repeat** - To do something again.\n"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "233eb40b-97b7-4408-9bf5-194520ea12a5",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5f4ff1f4-7394-4cdd-be9b-41621babf395"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "39d53202-1a81-4ce1-a6c0-bba90aae1b21",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We highly recommend pair programming for this lesson. This may not be an easy topic for the majority of your students. Working with a partner and discussing potential solutions to the puzzles might ease the students' minds.\r\n\r\nAlso, have paper and pencils nearby for students to write out their plan before coding. Some puzzles have a limit on the number of certain blocks you can use, so if students like to write out the long answer to find the repeats, paper can be useful.",
        "name": "Nested Loops in Maze"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "39d53202-1a81-4ce1-a6c0-bba90aae1b21",
        "lesson_activity.key": "188e0901-98c1-468c-8734-46a21ad05371"
      }
    },
