    {
      "key": "f87b8fa1-7817-493c-93e3-06281f316368",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Use these activities to enhance student learning. They can be used as outside of class activities or other enrichment.\n\n#### More Minecraft\n\nIf you find that your class really enjoys the _Minecraft_ environment, [here are some links to other _Minecraft_ games they can play online](https://code.org/minecraft). These games will also teach basic coding skills."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f87b8fa1-7817-493c-93e3-06281f316368",
        "lesson_activity.key": "90c4640a-5ff2-449c-8938-b053b2c0a48a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "03b1d8b7-553d-4f22-acc8-fae0101bbb18",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display**: Show “Reflect” slide\n\nReview the \"Conditionals with Cards\" activity with your students.\n\n- _What is a conditional statement?_\n- _When is it useful for you to use a conditional in your program?_",
        "name": "Introduction"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "03b1d8b7-553d-4f22-acc8-fae0101bbb18",
        "lesson_activity.key": "106d417b-8d18-4699-a945-b1533b4c0242"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ca46a1cd-f5a1-451a-8da7-b9a64028d792",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display**: Show “Preview - If/Else with Bee” slide\n\n**Say:** *Now we're going to use conditionals with the Code.org bee to help him deal with some mysterious clouds. We don't know if his flowers have nectar or not, so we'll need to use conditionals to make sure that we collect nectar if it's there, but that we don't try to collect nectar from a flower that doesn't have any.*\n\nPull up a puzzle from this lesson, we recommend puzzle 9. \n\n - Ask the class what the bee should do when it gets to the cloud.\n    - The bee should use a conditional to check for a flower or a honeycomb.\n - Use the \"if at flower / else block\". Ask the class what the bee should do if there's a flower. If there's not a flower, there will be a honeycomb. What should the bee do then?\n    - The bee should \"get nectar\" if there is a flower and \"make honey\" if there is a honeycomb.\n\nFill in the rest of the code and press \"Run\". Discuss with the class why this worked.",
        "name": "Preview of Online Puzzles \r"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
